To reveal the molecular-level mechanisms of C. reinhardtii exposed to CDs, DEGs in Control vs 0.5 mg/L-CDs were identified by transcriptome analysis and gene identification. A total of over 430 million clean reads were obtained (Table 2
                        ). The Q30 of the raw reads in all groups ranged from 92.55% to 94.76%, and Q20 was higher than 97.00%, meaning that the sequencing data was reliable for the subsequent analysis requirements. According to the results of the RNA transcriptome sequencing analysis, the 0.5 mg/L-CDs-treated C. reinhardtii uncovered 1166 DEGs, including 610 up-regulated and 556 down-regulated DEGs (Fig. 8
                        a). A cluster diagram showed the levels of many transcripts in two primary hierarchical clusters, labeled A and B, which revealed the differences in gene expression patterns in the control versus treatment groups (Fig. S7).
